title: Cognition
subject: Connecticut Early Learning and Development Standards (CT ELDS) (2014-)

document.title: Connecticut’s Early Learning and Development Standards

A4F0D72477364FD791017E2279F7A649.description:
Typically resists
impulses and can wait
longer to respond in more
structured settings (e.g., at
a restaurant, in circle time in
preschool)

4D9030CC558341149C66FCEEF7842FE9.description:
Engage in preferred
and some non-preferred
activities for longer periods
of time. Remain with some
high-interest activities 15
minutes or longer

DE9D6F8204854C979B3E54734CABFF02.description:
With adult
reminders can briefly
inhibit initial response
(e.g., stop imitating
inappropriate
behaviors of peers,
wait turn to respond
to question or prompt
in group setting)

E8192319FF564E41869511657B78C325.description:
Maintain
focus on high-interest
activities in the face
of minor social or
sensory distractions

8FC1D81A99E04705A3D5BEFBE10B732C.description:
With adult
support, resist impulses
in structured settings
for brief, but increasing
periods of time

FA3CFB1297974C13BE40C91F17629E75.description:
Maintain focus
on high-interest activities
in the face of routine
distractions

AE0144865B624F2A8F2C3E7BA184290B.description:
Engage in
interactions and self-selected
activities for increasing
length of time

2EE8304FDAEA4519B64952FD5E17B9C2.description:
Hold in mind the
topic of group discussion
and contribute personal
experience (e.g., when
talking about something that
is broken says, “My mom
used a screwdriver to fix our
shelf.”)

485A3E1883DE4D2EAE2ECB97EAB2C039.description:
Engage in
games that involve
remembering (e.g.,
memory)

C716ACCD72C04A8C81A8E9C81518ED6E.description:
Remember
where recently used
objects were placed

FB9B528363684D67AB6CBA64BC51529C.description:
Hold in mind a
simple task long enough to
complete it (e.g., wiping a
table, walking across the
room to throw something in
the garbage)

470504BA5EC242BB9B70DA859A1E7E14.description:
Generate or seek
out multiple solutions to a
problem

67520843278644D4B7022B4018D15248.description:
With adult
assistance, stop and
consider alternatives
when encountering a
problem

8FF0DAA260CB47348D735D5DC22BD4D3.description:
Realize when
something is not working
and with adult assistance
can try another approach

3E4E0AA1F19F46D6AB60E1280B1E1ECD.description:
Purposefully try
multiple ways of using the
same objects

8CCDAF6F80884FB58427B22E51B43D2D.description:
Use
objects in new and
unexpected ways

70303AD3D7144066B7E149EB8D304FB6.description:
Complete longer
term and more complex
tasks with a focus on the
goal, despite frustration

0C6AA564DF4D4913BB7C39FD287EDF03.description:
Continue
working through
moderately difficult
activities, despite
some frustration

ECEBFF7598DF4C8F9A149863B7EB4B58.description:
Complete selfselected short-term
activities many times to
gain mastery

5A98D219FABA460FB5FA148C06CFF175.description:
Practice an
activity many times
until successful

26F9F58F21054B2C84A45B9A5DE32FBE.description:
Repeat
actions to obtain
similar results

9A52A26D858F4603A673E6DB4AB323FE.description:
Make a plan, follow
through and review plan
based on what they actually
did. Indicate reasons for
choice, set goals and follow
plan

05B34007A57E4DBEBB6067F02BC25655.description:
With adult
assistance, choose
activities and plan
what to do

923350C1C3FF4CDEB271C613C89F179A.description:
Indicate
preferences by
pointing and using
one or two words

DFB64928AE204BEF92031DF01E112D35.description: Early learning experiences will support children to strengthen executive function.

2BEB5ABAF23849A590E8712764116F6A.description:
Represent people,
places or things through
drawings, movements
and/or three-dimensional
constructions that are
increasingly abstract (e.g.,
may draw a map that
includes an “X” that marks
the location of the treasure)

CDB89D9E76D447CCA844023701FD84F8.description:
Engage in extended
pretend play scenarios and
display recognition of the
difference between pretend
or fantasy situations and
reality

459F6CCFC9374C3D94466EC1F077D706.description:
Use dissimilar
objects to represent other
objects in play or perform
an action with an imaginary
object (e.g., use stirring
action without anything in
hand)

AF53201D7FB34292AB0E95220CD86036.description:
Represent
people, places
or things through
simple drawings,
movements and
three-dimensional
construction

96A89692157B4FF6A3A020AAF654E87F.description:
Act out
actions or scenarios
involving familiar
roles (e.g., teacher,
doctor, firefighter)

44273CE373BA4B58BB793D9DA58D426F.description:
Use or make
a prop to represent
an object (e.g., build
a telephone)

CE2871BB079C4F66A7856118E392181B.description:
Act out relational
roles in play (e.g., mom
or dad with baby)

1DB8CD337CD8452286444BF66A90B247.description:
Use a similar
object to represent
another object in play
(e.g., pretend a pencil is
a spoon)

CD27563A78F446FBBEFF1A38A7567ECA.description:
Act out familiar
functions in play (e.g.,
sweeping floor, pouring milk)

BB86781A02A840E2B3964D66CA056032.description:
Play with dolls or
stuffed animals and realistic
props together (e.g., use a
play spoon to feed a doll)

09CD052360BD42A2A5EB03CB0A009566.description:
Engage in
pretend play with
realistic objects
(e.g., uses a play
phone to pretend
to make a phone
call)

EE947808C9C04FE2BDD6258A57DE5532.description:
Use
dolls and stuffed
animals as if they
were real (e.g.,
rocks doll, pets
stuffed dog)

4B2BB845D6F74BA4BF5B8D5B38E4E9E3.description:
Try multiple
strategies to solve a problem
and draw on multiple
resources (e.g., look at what
a peer is doing for ideas)

D06D213482D44A54942B3B046EB6AFC1.description:
Think of and
try an alternative
strategy when a
first attempt at
solving a problem is
unsuccessful

AC4FCDA5CFAF4CE0848FD92E4DF42DEB.description:
Use spatial
relationships to solve
problems (e.g., fit pieces
into puzzle)

5D0F17E380CD4111980397869C2BB27A.description:
Use objects in
new and unexpected
ways to solve problems
through trial and error

597218BC1F92453A966283C3FD5A2491.description:
Take things apart and
try to put them back together

90D4536C5EDB47BBB9D0630C3C4681C1.description:
Try a successful
strategy in a new situation
(e.g., tugging or prying on
something that is stuck)

F30BD7DC66F1460197DA0BBF118A1C8C.description:
Utilize
shapes and
sorting boxes.
May use trial and
error to fit objects
together

9B65A717D4374F2F8C823DAFFCAD0998.description:
Purposefully
experiment with
the effects of
new actions upon
objects

8DE4947C824F493A9090D6E9B120F62E.description:
Solve
simple manipulative
challenges through
observation and
imitation (e.g., putting
something “into a
bucket”)

D20F3815FE2946579D58073A1AC9E581.description:
Use a variety
of actions to obtain
desired objects

D4F46A835FD84AA8A5949208C4CE6F7E.description:
Sometimes
will show they
can solve
problems by
reaching for
desired toys or
blanket

5CC6A5D479F247B5809073B6DAA698F5.description:
Begin to question
accuracy of information
and sources as evidenced
by sharing conflicting
information from another
source (e.g., when the
teacher shares information
with class, says, “But my
dad says…”)

FC984837373443CE954A55E1DE702018.description:
Use familiar patterns
to solve problems and
reason (e.g., if we go to the
library every other day and
we went yesterday, today
we will...)

530BBB970C554DC5AFCD279F9A2AEDDE.description:
Compare relative
attributes of objects, people,
events, sounds (e.g.,
louder, more, less)

C1B4AF17667F4E8FBFD550BAAD4F0871.description:
Recognize
patterns in routines,
objects and/or
sounds and replicate
sequence using
objects or language

F9F385AAE22345208112952F22899802.description:
Identify
similarities and
differences in objects,
people, events,
sounds based on one
attribute (e.g., same
or different colors,
loud or soft sound)

A850E43FE67A4DE1A27BF0FC3AB3974F.description:
Identify differences
between objects across
multiple characteristics
(e.g., texture, color,
shape, size)

8B6B9F55194142E0B47437734BCD070C.description:
Sort objects by type
(e.g., cars and blocks) and
put some objects in order
(e.g., lines up three objects
from smallest to biggest)

E939CA24115145A4B5514C53BE32EA9C.description:
Match objects
that are the same
(simple categorizing)

B5B0A835D2294F6291BD0B55AA3A3A78.description:
Respond
to new or
novel objects
with interest,
recognizing
differences

54F8EDD31E844892A539AB2CBA26A0F4.description:
Recognize
familiar people
or objects in
the immediate
environment (e.g.,
notice differences
between various
people and
objects)

2D9FC88AD9594DA793525FBCAB970365.description:
Try multiple uses
of same materials and
observe differing results

20ED58A5980E468299D3309E160EE3D4.description:
Manipulate
materials and
communicate about
the impact of own
actions

741CA72308704B1B96C05BD0CB1700A9.description:
Vary actions to
observe different results
(e.g., hit lever harder to
see if result changes)

7D170DD78CD043B3AA947897BE3DF43C.description:
Repeat actions over
and over and notice results

E38B9D284E5B4F32972AA1616F8F2040.description:
Learn
by observing or
listening to others
and repeating
their actions or
verbalizations

705919974FC1415985DF24201026EF2A.description:
Recognize
effect of actions
on object - cause
and effect (e.g.,
shake a rattle and it
makes a sound)

07A753C323D44C27AB9252E767BB6AA4.description:
Show
interest in the
results of their
actions and
“accidental”
discoveries

A9A2084F6E01427A9D12DFCCCA578218.description: Early learning experiences will support children to use logic and reasoning.

30F30641565C44B3B46FDA7DD1766C45.description:
Model or teach peers
how to use materials or
complete a task

EE6EF82A8FB54BF4ABBB912E639050B6.description:
Plan and complete
learning activity with a peer

61425D99C3844C8A894CAC2F5E128507.description:
Engage in and
complete learning activities
with peers

7A141ADB17F946A389E48FA9C8F3BBB2.description:
Cooperation
with Peers
in Learning
Experiences

42EEB5F9B377415191B561C551242B20.description:
Show pride in
accomplishment when
reaching mastery of a skill
and share experiences with
others

2F319F7FCD564DFDB67AFA8CA34D370E.description:
Seek out new
challenges and novel
experiences

0F0D746D35894AB28A9696C79EE8C9A0.description:
Demonstrate
enthusiasm for new
learning (may be within
familiar contexts)

4811BBBF16BB4E6A8CA71C48A7747CA5.description:
Demonstrate
a desire to
accomplish a new
skill. May look to
others for approval
and congratulations

175BD71EFDCF4CB48B9D5C032EDDC20A.description:
Explore new
ways to use objects
and observe results

DD06A1BB5C4442238FE30077694F4E76.description:
Seek out
new materials and
experiences

AB53E70F9C66485DACC96B9FE852C62E.description:
Laugh,
babble, increase
movement,
and engage in
repetition of a
learning activity

A34BF6BC5EFF4CC7AF19B7284913E498.description:
Engage in preferred
and some non-preferred
activities for longer periods
of time. Remain with some
high interest activities 15
minutes or longer

328023458E1E4CB29009178FE683D7EE.description:
Express interest in
learning about a specific
topic over time

1B3E0BA4F35646988414473375344587.description:
Maintain interest in
exploring specific topics over
time

4DF9BFB8157A4D27B136ACB1E7339685.description:
Maintain interest
in self-selected activities
and may seek to engage
others or ask questions

393984724214446499AA2931F7F6E782.description:
Engage
in interactions
and self-selected
activities for
increasing lengths
of time

611E647FC2524545B315DA3ABAF1B883.description:
Focus
attention on
interesting sights
or sounds, often in
shared experiences
with adults

FCCF755062AC4D16ABD02BF2114E9455.description:
Show
interest in a wider
variety of sights
and sounds with
greater purpose,
often in shared
experiences with
adults

2ACB7B14B6DC47E081935245FEE30BFC.description:
Orient to
source of sound
or movement
and vocalize in
response to sights
and sounds in
the immediate
environment

C35F448FDD764AA1B229E0FF4E9B3CA9.description:
Engagement
with
Environment,
People and
Objects

55839D16DA904EDEAAC7B3EBD745FB61.description:
Investigate ways to
make something happen

52704EECB834415AA04A01341248BA15.description:
Explore and investigate
a variety of experiences and
topics using different materials

E22A979DD48A42CFB44C77555BA34896.description:
Ask questions
and seek answers from a
variety of sources

946EB488272646EE896D16E564FEDD40.description:
Use
senses to actively
investigate and
explore the effects
of new actions on
objects

2863494D94F24BC89ECEEF56F23C9D0A.description:
Seek
familiar people
and/or objects that
are not there

416DD5A59CEE4A3EBA05752DAF96BCF0.description:
Use
senses to explore
immediate
environment

6C98FFA2F26144C99C7B2D9DDF85E8E4.description: Early learning experiences will support children to develop effective approaches to learning.
